#eNCA Courtesy #DStv403 CAPE TOWN - The Correctional Services Department says its dealing with overcrowding in prisons and is now set on tackling the officials to inmates’ ratio. A probe into the escape of inmates from the Malmesbury Medium A prison facility in Cape Town led to the axing of 94 officials in 2021 for aiding escapes and smuggling illegal substances. In 2020 ago 69 inmates escaped the prison while a further two prisoners escaped in 2021 and another three just last week. READ: Correctional Services | DCS says it's addressed overcrowding, infrastructure challenges The Police and Prisons Civil Rights Union provincial spokesperson, Patrick Raolane, says heads must roll. He says the lives of witnesses and the public are at risk. One security expert says overcrowding and certain limitations of movement due to the coronavirus pandemic may also play a factor in the escapes. The department says it has dealt with the issue of overcrowding in prisons. And it is currently working on plans to hire more staff to deal with the officials to inmates’ ratio. Watch the video above for more details on this story.